Now, to answer the question of I know you just asked. What the hell is a gnomeathon. Well I'll tell you.  It's simply a race from Ak'Anon to Lavastorm. <br>
Of course there is a catch. You will do it as level 1 gnomes. There are more rules, but don't worry, it will still be fun. The rules are as follows. <br>
All participants must make level 1 gnomes. Necros and Shadow Knights are the only classes allowed. No it isn't impossible. Hard but not impossible.<br>
The name you chose must start with DC.<br>
No anons or roleplayings. The officials (if I can find some) will need to know where you are.<br>
You must get there on your own. Clarification is as follows.  The only buffs or equipment you are allowed will be that you start with as a new character. SKs start with no spells and necros start with 2 I believe. Those are the only spell I want to see used during the race. No buying upgrade equipment. Your character should have no money to spend, which brings me to the next rule.<br>
No looting anything you kill. No one can use the excuse &quot;I got a sow potion with the money I got for the mobs I killed.<br>
So no one gets confused, level one necros and shadow knights do not get any type of sow, invis or camo so none should have any of these effects on them at any time.<br>
Once again, no &quot;outside&quot; aid. You must get to Lavestorm on your own power. The exception being the boats or the spires to the nexus. Yes I said the nexus is ok and good luck to any that wish to use it. This also means NO PORTS as neither necros nor sk's get them.<br>
No short cuts through &quot;safe&quot; territory. You must follow the paths or road. The two exceptions being Freeport and Nectolos forest. You may get through these places using any route you can find except porting.<br>
Time will be given to necros to scribe and mem their spells.<br>
Now the fun part. To help discourage &quot;accidental or &quot;unasked for&quot; buffs, the race will begins only after all participants talk to the Priest of Discord and becomes PVP ready. The race will start at the Priest of discord.  Please, no killing other contestants till the race gets started.<br>
Now. Once the race starts, as long as you don't break any rules, you are free to make your way to Lavastorm as you see fit. Just remember, Harm touch alone is not enough to kill a level one character as it only does 11 points of damage.<br>
If the race takes to long or gets bogged down cause of some unforeseen event (like boats screwing up again) I may call a total free for all and a suspension of all rules.<br>
A chat channel will be given before the race.<br>
I will need a few &quot;officials&quot; to help out and make sure no one cheats as there will be a prize. You will be told before hand what it will be.<br>
If you have a problem or disagree with any rules I have stated, tough. But I can be bribed. hehe. but seriously. I'm just trying to have a fun event and I am flexible if you can show me a better way. If There is no interest in this event, then I will not sponsor the Scavenger hunt/bake off I have in mind nor the group scavenger hunt nor the Raid on the warrens I had in mind. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
